net.smacke.jaydio.channel

Class MockByteChannel

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.smacke.jaydio.channel.MockByteChannel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable, Channel, BufferedChannel<JaydioByteBuffer>

    public final class MockByteChannel
extends Object
implements BufferedChannel<JaydioByteBuffer>
    A mock implementation of BufferedChannel, to be used for testing. The mock channel is backed file, located on java heap.

    Author:
    smacke

      • getChannel

        public static MockByteChannel getChannel(long length,
                         int blockSize,
                         boolean readOnly)
        Factory method returning a new MockByteChannel.

        Parameters:
        length - The maximum length that the "file" will grow to -- this is how many bytes will be allocated on Java heap
        blockSize - The block size of the fake file system for this fake file
        readOnly - Whether this "channel" is in readOnly mode
        Returns:
        A new MockByteChannel with the corresponding parameters
